The era of quarterbacking that's actually gone is the era where star quarterbacks are guys who are pocket exclusive, that might as well be a relic. But to me pocket QBs are still alive and thriving, being found in QBs that can also improv making plays outside of structure.

I know a lot of people see Mahomes as a physical god, but he's also a phenomenal pocket passer. That's what allowed 13 seconds to happen plus the OT game winner. Allen's also progressed into an excellent pocket passer as well.

Guys like Mahomes, Allen, Burrow, Dak, Stafford, etc are more than capable of making plays outside the pocket, some way more than others, but the reason teams pay and trade for them to get them to the playoffs is because they all can make the throws in the pocket too.

Here's a take I actually believe: Despite what a lot of people *seem* to believe, I don't think the era of pocket QBs are gone. In fact, I see them as more relevant than ever, just with expanded skill sets.

Do I deserve to get cooked for this take? Absolutely, it’s unrealistic and doesn’t appreciate guys that are on the outside looking in on the top 10.
